      <head>Richard Specht</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian writer about music and music critic.</p>

        <p>Specht studied piano with Ignaz Br√ºll and composition with Zemlinsky and
          Schreker. In 1909, he founded the journal <ref cRef="merker_der"><title level="j">Der Merker</title></ref>, the chief
          editor of which he remained until 1919; he was music critic of the Viennese daily 
          <ref cRef="zeit_die_wien"><title level="j">Die Zeit</title></ref> 1904-08, wrote for <ref cRef="musik_die"><title>Die Musik</title></ref> 1908-15,
          and for the <title level="j">Illustrirte Wiener Extrablatt</title> 1912-20. He wrote
          biographies of several composers, and many introductions to operas and orchestral works.</p>
        
        <p>No correspondence between Specht and Schenker is known to survive.</p>
      </div>
